1. Description:
enc is a simple manager written in bash simplifying work with EncFS encryption software.

2. Usage:
	enc <stash> [mount_point] # Mount the stash
	enc add <stash> [dir] # Add new stash identified by name <stash>, optionally set the location of data directory outside the enc directory.
	enc psw <stash> # Change password for the <stash>
	enc del <stash> # Delete the <stash>
	enc zip <stash> <output> # Archive (zip) the <stash>
	enc size <stash> # Get size of the <stash>

3. Installation:
Run install.sh script with root privileges or copy the enc.sh manualy into /usr/bin folder.

4. Requirements:
encfs >= 1.7.4
encfsctl >= 1.7.4 (should be part of encfs)
zip (tested with 3.0 but it should work fine even with older versions)

5. Links
EncFS homepage - http://www.arg0.net/encfs
enc git repository - https://bitbucket.org/erlcash/enc/overview
